<p>My entry on Log of Anomalous Items, Vol II:<br />
<strong>Item Description:</strong> A toilet with cognitohazardous properties. Individuals will uniformly be reluctant to flush the toilet, as exposed individuals have a significant suspicion that a malevolent entity of some kind might use the sound of the flush to conceal the sound of its own approach before attacking. This effect is weak enough that most individuals will dismiss it as irrational and flush the toilet. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">No evidence supporting the existence of any malevolent entities connected to the toilet has been found.</span> In light of a recent experiment, the Foundation's understanding of this object is being re-evaluated.<br />
<strong>Date of Recovery:</strong> 04-11-2017<br />
